I mean, I'm not saying that, you know, go ahead if you wish, but maybe there should be a little bit of a study on this so that we have a better perspective on where we're coming from and where we are going.

661
00:55:36,732 --> 00:55:48,455
There has to be, I'll tell you a little insert, in the Haverhill, the mayor of Haverhill during February of 22, they had a plowing problem with this odd and even

662
00:55:52,243 --> 00:55:53,444
a plan in place.

663
00:55:54,264 --> 00:55:57,007
And the plows could not, it was on the even side.

664
00:55:57,067 --> 00:55:59,769
Everybody had a park on the even side that was permanent.

665
00:56:01,410 --> 00:56:07,135
The snow plows came down and they weren't able to do the whole even side.

666
00:56:07,896 --> 00:56:08,797
So the next day

667
00:56:09,958 --> 00:56:19,260
They went back and all of the people who were correctly and legally parked on the even side had to move over to the odd side so the snow plows could finish their work.

668
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:21,880
There has to be flexibility in this.

669
00:56:22,680 --> 00:56:24,460
It can't be just etched in stone.

670
00:56:24,781 --> 00:56:29,461
There are going to be circumstances throughout the years where things are going to have to remain flexible.

671
00:56:30,862 --> 00:56:33,622
And I myself have been a victim.

672
00:56:33,982 --> 00:56:38,963
Yes, victimized by driveway entries and exits.

673
00:56:39,748 --> 00:56:48,773
out of my own driveway with bumper and bumper cars on the odd side of the driveway, as well as abutting my own driveway.

674
00:56:50,014 --> 00:56:52,155
Talking about law and enforcement.

675
00:56:53,075 --> 00:56:57,678
All right, it's impossible in the winter, I know, for three feet distance from a driveway.

676
00:56:58,058 --> 00:57:01,520
I understand that, but they are overlapping a driveway.

677
00:57:02,340 --> 00:57:07,363
What's going to happen if all of the cars have to park on the odd side of the driveway?

678
00:57:08,713 --> 00:57:16,019
Don't you think they're going to squeeze in to any space they can, even if it is overlapping the driveway?

679
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:21,403
And then what happens to the resident in their home who's trying to get out to go to work?

680
00:57:23,318 --> 00:57:26,000
John, I appreciate the comments and your participation.

681
00:57:26,360 --> 00:57:30,042
That was a deep look into the issue.

682
00:57:30,062 --> 00:57:33,424
There's two questions you asked.

683
00:57:33,504 --> 00:57:35,125
I just want to make sure I answer them for you first.

684
00:57:35,325 --> 00:57:38,207
One, enforcement is done by the Medford Police Department.

685
00:57:38,427 --> 00:57:45,792
And two, while historically there are people in the city who still use that or adhere to the concept of spacecrafts,

686
00:57:46,732 --> 00:57:48,634
The Medford police does not condone it.

687
00:57:48,674 --> 00:57:50,215
The DPW does not condone it.

688
00:57:50,595 --> 00:57:54,697
And we cannot allow those things to happen as it moves forward.

689
00:57:55,137 --> 00:57:58,099
So, but I really, really do appreciate your comments on this.

690
00:57:58,219 --> 00:57:59,940
Anyone else against the petition?

691
00:58:00,421 --> 00:58:02,282
Chief, can you just explain for me?

692
00:58:03,903 --> 00:58:10,527
I think that the term space grab, I've heard of space savers and that's the thing you put in the space to save it.

693
00:58:10,647 --> 00:58:13,569
And my understanding is we don't allow that in Medford.

694
00:58:13,849 --> 00:58:14,109
Correct.

695
00:58:14,149 --> 00:58:15,670
That's the interpretation.

696
00:58:16,246 --> 00:58:20,867
The resident meant people were grabbing the space she had shoveled out.

697
00:58:21,708 --> 00:58:25,309
And that's what she was objecting to, that she wasn't able to save the space.

698
00:58:25,329 --> 00:58:31,991
Well, we could refer back to her for comment, but either way, I mean, I get it.

699
00:58:32,011 --> 00:58:38,693
I mean, it puts the city and the police department in a very difficult position to have to say,

700
00:58:39,923 --> 00:58:43,005
I mean, it's public streets, public parking, residents have the right to park.

701
00:58:43,025 --> 00:58:49,268
We can never sit there and say, you have an entitlement to park in the street, even if you shovel it up.

702
00:58:49,448 --> 00:58:54,350
I mean, I think neighborhoods resolve those issues sometimes themselves, but if you involve the police, we only have one option.

703
00:58:54,370 --> 00:58:56,051
It's public street and public parking.

704
00:58:56,491 --> 00:59:02,334
So, and I think either way would be handled by the police department in the same manner.

705
00:59:03,855 --> 00:59:04,335
Thank you.

706
00:59:05,556 --> 00:59:07,637
Anyone else wishing to speak against the petition?

707
00:59:07,949 --> 00:59:08,789
I have to slide down.

708
00:59:09,049 --> 00:59:09,850
This is Sheila.

709
00:59:10,870 --> 00:59:12,250
Sheila, I'm going to ask you to unmute.

710
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:14,811
Sheila, welcome.

711
00:59:18,092 --> 00:59:19,573
Sheila, just got unmuted on your phone.

712
00:59:19,593 --> 00:59:25,415
So I agree with Joan.

713
00:59:25,875 --> 00:59:35,138
I think it's not fair to the residents on the even side that it should be on each side each year.

714
00:59:35,298 --> 00:59:36,398
It should change every year.

715
00:59:36,973 --> 00:59:47,256
And then the even side residents have to contend with the snow being piled up on their side, and I just don't think it's fair to the residents on the even side of the street.

716
00:59:48,896 --> 00:59:50,577
Well, I'm in opposition of it as well.

717
00:59:51,597 --> 00:59:54,818
Sheila, thank you for your participation in your comments.

718
00:59:57,159 --> 00:59:59,760
Anyone else should speak against it?

719
01:00:00,360 --> 01:00:00,480
Gary.

720
01:00:05,843 --> 01:00:06,823
Just got on mute guys.

721
01:00:06,843 --> 01:00:08,884
I mean, Kathy.

722
01:00:09,004 --> 01:00:19,228
I'm going to ask you to unmute and then you can unmute it.

723
01:00:24,750 --> 01:00:25,570
Hi, I get it.

724
01:00:26,411 --> 01:00:32,593
Uh, I just want to, I just want to say that, um, I think that Joan put it extremely well.

725
01:00:33,625 --> 01:00:42,832
There is real problems at this part of the street because of how narrow it is and how many trucks and cars and stuff like that, that are on this part of the street.

726
01:00:44,033 --> 01:00:46,115
And one of the things too.

727
01:00:46,896 --> 01:00:52,500
One of the things too it's actually very interesting because you're actually having two different parts of the street that are arguing one thing.

728
01:00:52,980 --> 01:00:55,402
in a different part of the street that's arguing something else.

729
01:00:56,703 --> 01:01:07,672
And I know that they have brought, I know they've brought the police up here before because we have people with out of state plates that are parking here overnight and they don't do anything about it.

730
01:01:08,052 --> 01:01:09,573
And I don't even think that's legal to do.

731
01:01:10,854 --> 01:01:15,138
I mean, so my question would be who's actually enforcing the parking?

732
01:01:17,539 --> 01:01:20,001
That is the Medford Police Department.

733
01:01:20,021 --> 01:01:25,964
I think you need to have a conversation with the Medford Police Department as to why they don't enforce it.

734
01:01:26,044 --> 01:01:26,525
I don't know.

735
01:01:28,486 --> 01:01:30,787
Specifically just parking in general?

736
01:01:30,947 --> 01:01:33,008
No, they're parking overnight on the street.

737
01:01:33,029 --> 01:01:38,752
They leave it overnight on the street and the plates are from New Hampshire.

738
01:01:41,258 --> 01:01:42,439
All right, Chief, can I address this?

739
01:01:42,939 --> 01:01:43,599
Please, Sergeant.

740
01:01:43,839 --> 01:01:47,281
I spoke to the owner of that truck in question.

741
01:01:47,321 --> 01:01:50,242
He's claiming that he does not stay here.

742
01:01:50,262 --> 01:01:54,224
Well, then I would send a police cruiser up around here to check it.

743
01:01:54,885 --> 01:02:00,547
And it's not just a... Sir, this is not a forum for argument.

744
01:02:00,607 --> 01:02:01,428
You brought an issue up.

745
01:02:01,508 --> 01:02:03,289
I need to have my traffic sergeant address it.

746
01:02:03,489 --> 01:02:03,809
Thank you.

747
01:02:04,994 --> 01:02:06,715
Chief, I spoke to the owner of that truck.

748
01:02:06,755 --> 01:02:08,635
He said he lives in New Hampshire.

749
01:02:08,675 --> 01:02:10,516
He visits his girlfriend now and then.

750
01:02:10,536 --> 01:02:20,258
He does not live at 70 Gaston Street, and therefore he is not required to register his place in Massachusetts.

751
01:02:21,799 --> 01:02:23,939
I spoke to him, I believe it was last Sunday.

752
01:02:24,319 --> 01:02:24,819
Okay.

753
01:02:28,920 --> 01:02:32,642
So it's Gary and Kathy, and I'll just leave it this way.

754
01:02:32,843 --> 01:02:34,864
I will have my traffic sergeant reach out to you.

755
01:02:36,245 --> 01:02:46,111
In some sense, this isn't exactly pertained to what we're discussing here, the odd even parking issues, but you do have an argument and a legitimate concern that if there are cars that are parking on the street, it's not.

756
01:02:46,131 --> 01:02:55,337
So I'll have the traffic sergeants reach out to you separately so we don't take up time on the commission meeting to handle that as it relates to the police department.

757
01:02:55,437 --> 01:02:58,519
Is there anyone else wishing to speak in opposition?

758
01:02:59,970 --> 01:03:01,932
I think somebody someone else with you.

759
01:03:02,252 --> 01:03:02,452
Yep.

760
01:03:02,492 --> 01:03:02,753
Go ahead.

761
01:03:02,793 --> 01:03:03,533
We'll open it up.

762
01:03:03,934 --> 01:03:04,354
There you go.

763
01:03:06,636 --> 01:03:07,197
Welcome again.

764
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:09,079
Hi, it's Kathy Floyd.

765
01:03:09,679 --> 01:03:15,124
I can't all of the additional cars and trucks and everything affects the parking.

766
01:03:16,185 --> 01:03:16,606
No, yep.

767
01:03:16,686 --> 01:03:24,053
I'm just trying to recognize whether or not it's a snow emergency or whether it's it's not in there is a car that is parking with the answer plates.

768
01:03:27,554 --> 01:03:28,114
Okay, understood.

769
01:03:28,174 --> 01:03:29,816
Anyone else wishing to speak in opposition?

770
01:03:33,138 --> 01:03:36,261
Seeing none, could we, can you flip the second page?

771
01:03:36,301 --> 01:03:36,861
Sorry about that.

772
01:03:37,021 --> 01:03:37,422
Anyone else?

773
01:03:37,642 --> 01:03:39,984
We didn't see anyone there, okay.

774
01:03:40,024 --> 01:03:42,105
Turn it back to the commissioners for comments or questions.

775
01:03:44,927 --> 01:03:45,588
I have a question.

776
01:03:47,229 --> 01:03:48,990
Just to clarify, what are we doing now?

777
01:03:49,411 --> 01:03:51,052
It's one year odd, one year even?

778
01:03:51,592 --> 01:03:52,273
Correct, yes.

779
01:03:52,453 --> 01:03:52,773
Okay.

780
01:03:53,154 --> 01:03:53,314
Yep.

781
01:03:53,974 --> 01:03:57,337
And who makes these initial determinations on what side of the street?

782
01:03:58,383 --> 01:03:59,184
should be parking.

783
01:03:59,544 --> 01:04:21,062
So the long-standing traffic commission process is the winter starts in say 2022 like this year it is even side parking the winter starts next year and say 2023 it's odd side parking that has been in play for in my entire 25 years career and it's during snow emergencies Sergeant Rogers said 40 years so but in this situation equity issues

784
01:04:21,718 --> 01:04:26,819
In situations where you create safety hazards as a result of the choices.

785
01:04:26,839 --> 01:04:40,062
I mean, is there another group, maybe Tim's group who weighs in on like, uh, the one gentleman mentioned that when traffic or when snow plowings on one direction going to.

786
01:04:40,082 --> 01:04:43,983
Uh, bracket street, I think he mentioned becomes like a safety hazard.

787
01:04:44,143 --> 01:04:50,384
Are there some situations where the odd even really doesn't work because you create safety issues when you switch it?

788
01:04:53,333 --> 01:04:55,115
So, yeah, so it's a good question.

789
01:04:55,215 --> 01:05:03,924
I can't think of one offhand with that's currently in that play and I know that's one of the arguments being made to us before us tonight but I can't think of one offhand that's made to it.

790
01:05:04,464 --> 01:05:14,114
There are some locations in the city, where we choose one side, every single year and that's generally because there's like a park across the street.

791
01:05:14,818 --> 01:05:20,080
and a certain street might have a public park across the street and residents park in front of their house year round.

792
01:05:20,700 --> 01:05:24,902
Um, that, that seems to be the, probably the biggest exception to this rule.

793
01:05:25,042 --> 01:05:28,063
Otherwise it is odd even across the city.

794
01:05:28,684 --> 01:05:28,904
Yeah.

795
01:05:30,484 --> 01:05:36,427
Uh, you know, I think this is a prime example of equity and I don't necessarily know that there's unanimity on what

796
01:05:37,456 --> 01:05:38,477
the street needs.

797
01:05:38,578 --> 01:05:58,058
So absent some sort of safety issue that's created when traffic is one way or another, which I don't necessarily think this committee is in a position to rule on, I think that's more of a public's work, not to give Tim more things to do, but to evaluate that there are true safety issues that come when the parking is on one side versus the other.

798
01:05:58,822 --> 01:06:02,865
You know, unfortunately in this city, what you deal with is exactly what you're dealing with.

799
01:06:02,885 --> 01:06:04,846
Streets are narrow, there are way too many cars.

800
01:06:04,926 --> 01:06:08,888
So switching this to one side of the street, I don't think solves the problem.

801
01:06:09,169 --> 01:06:15,873
Again, absent the safety issue, which in that case, I don't think it's our position to actually rule on that, so.

802
01:06:17,474 --> 01:06:18,735
Thank you, Commissioner Brzezinski.

803
01:06:19,215 --> 01:06:22,017
Commissioner McGibbon, Commissioner Hunt?

804
01:06:22,037 --> 01:06:23,238
Yeah, I get a couple of things, I guess.

805
01:06:26,047 --> 01:06:40,925
It was brought up and I am aware of this there's more parking spaces on the odd side than the even side that that's a factor here, and I would say Steve it's more of a operational challenges, when it comes to where to put snow and how to push it.

806
01:06:41,666 --> 01:06:44,468
And I think a couple of the residents on both sides that brought that up.

807
01:06:45,429 --> 01:06:57,937
So we try not to plow into the vehicles if we don't have to, we do try to remove and clear the snow, so push it to a place, as opposed to just pile up the wind rose inside.

808
01:06:57,957 --> 01:07:02,660
You know, but we're, we're limited because of the narrow streets.

809
01:07:03,080 --> 01:07:05,102
So, you know,

810
01:07:06,840 --> 01:07:12,845
Also, what has been said a couple times it's really about equity that's where this policy comes from.

811
01:07:14,546 --> 01:07:30,718
What is interesting in this situation is the difference of the sides of the street, where the houses are higher on one side with no off street parking or very little off street parking and then the other side, less parking spaces on street and more off street.

812
01:07:31,279 --> 01:07:34,441
So that makes this a little, little interesting.

813
01:07:36,235 --> 01:07:43,286
As, as well as the idea that 32 of the homes signed a petition that would like this.

814
01:07:49,180 --> 01:07:51,462
So I kind of have a couple questions.

815
01:07:51,642 --> 01:07:56,667
One is, do we know how many more parking spaces are on the odd side versus the even side?

816
01:07:57,367 --> 01:08:09,298
And then my next question is, do we know the reason why the other portion of Gaston Street was granted this variance, I guess you could call it?

817
01:08:11,564 --> 01:08:13,906
I, we do not have the answer to either one of those questions.

818
01:08:14,006 --> 01:08:16,307
And I suggest it probably would.

819
01:08:17,007 --> 01:08:19,429
Wouldn't be difficult to obtain them, but we're not going to get that.

820
01:08:19,629 --> 01:08:20,149
Okay.

821
01:08:20,610 --> 01:08:25,813
Commissioner Hunt.

822
01:08:27,314 --> 01:08:27,814
Yeah.

823
01:08:27,914 --> 01:08:29,375
I guess I come down to.

824
01:08:31,688 --> 01:08:34,469
if this would be easy if all the residents were in favor.

825
01:08:35,529 --> 01:08:41,470
Given that there are some who are strongly opposed, I feel like then it really comes down to safety and operations.

826
01:08:41,990 --> 01:08:49,552
And if this was coming from originally from Tim's office, like look, this would make a huge operational difference, then that would make a big deal.

827
01:08:49,572 --> 01:08:52,313
I think that if there is any

828
01:08:52,897 --> 01:09:03,026
information on such or who would give information on the safety issue because I am concerned about the cars that slide and stuff and that it's worse and it gets worse.

829
01:09:03,606 --> 01:09:10,532
And I do want to just actually point out one thing that I picked up on that residents pointed out that's changed here.

830
01:09:11,153 --> 01:09:12,614
And what's changed is that

831
01:09:14,948 --> 01:09:26,217
They, part of this road is relatively steep and they've made it very clear that it is, if not safe, they don't feel comfortable driving down in one direction or up in one direction.

832
01:09:26,237 --> 01:09:28,479
They have trouble in ice and snow.

833
01:09:29,300 --> 01:09:41,110
I also live in Fulton Heights, so I'm familiar with other, I'm not familiar with this street specific issue, but there are streets, my own, that I will only exit in one direction during snow events.

834
01:09:42,090 --> 01:09:46,654
because of exactly this, you'll slide into the intersection if you go down it.

835
01:09:46,694 --> 01:09:48,555
So we do have streets that are like this, I know it.

836
01:09:50,256 --> 01:09:58,302
But the key thing that's changed here is that in Medford, traditionally, nobody has ever cared which side of the street you park in on facing in which direction.

837
01:09:59,223 --> 01:10:09,490
And that is actually something that our current traffic department has stated is a safety issue, that if you park on the wrong side, facing the wrong way on the side of the road, that that's a safety issue.

838
01:10:09,911 --> 01:10:12,774
and therefore they feel very strongly about ticketing for it.

839
01:10:14,395 --> 01:10:15,917
And that is new this year.

840
01:10:16,717 --> 01:10:34,394
And if that's in fact causing people to now have to park in a way that then means that they're not feeling safe and they're having to slide down the hill or they can't, sorry, I didn't quite follow which years it's a problem in which direction, but it was my understanding from the way that the residents discussed this,

841
01:10:35,255 --> 01:10:49,448
the odd side of the street parking or the even side would alleviate that issue, allow you to be facing in the direction you're going to slide and not be sliding backwards down the hill if you were to park over there.

842
01:10:50,489 --> 01:11:11,345
And that it sounded to me maybe, I don't know if we need to confirm this or not, that in previous years, people just parked on the even side or parked on the side of the correct side of the street and if necessary, pointed their car in the direction that they felt was safest for sliding down the hill, not the way that's legally required.

843
01:11:12,626 --> 01:11:13,507
And that actually.

844
01:11:14,457 --> 01:11:15,777
It's something that changed.

845
01:11:15,837 --> 01:11:18,118
Why is it an issue this year and it never was before?

846
01:11:19,518 --> 01:11:33,542
And I think that we should actually consider that, that the enforcement of the rule of parking in the correct direction may have actually increased the dangerousness of parking on that street, on that side of the street during snow events.

847
01:11:34,482 --> 01:11:36,223
I feel that that's what I was hearing.

848
01:11:37,772 --> 01:11:39,793
And that makes me a little concerned about this.

849
01:11:40,833 --> 01:11:47,456
I do feel like, well, we could do more research, we could get some safety numbers, we could get some information on accident reports or whatever.

850
01:11:47,856 --> 01:11:55,539
If people even mention accidents, I mean, I certainly don't report it every time I slide into the intersection of Fulton Street, because I've gone the wrong way.

851
01:11:57,219 --> 01:11:59,360
But if I hit another car, hopefully I would.

852
01:12:00,500 --> 01:12:15,632
On the other hand, we're at the start of the month that is one of the snowiest months of the year and this is when it's going to be a problem is during February I'm very sorry that we were not talking about this in May or November, and would feel like we had more time to think about it.

853
01:12:17,013 --> 01:12:19,474
We should to address your first couple questions there.

854
01:12:20,235 --> 01:12:23,317
If we were to like table is to a date certain, I could also ask.

855
01:12:24,863 --> 01:12:31,907
my crews if there are issues on this particular stretch and if there are operation and safety issues on this stretch.

856
01:12:32,848 --> 01:12:37,931
I don't think there is, but getting their perspective may be helpful in this particular situation.

857
01:12:37,951 --> 01:12:45,576
So, and I would say that I think it's always been a rule to park in the direction of travel.

858
01:12:46,709 --> 01:12:48,030
I think it just hasn't been enforced.

859
01:12:48,670 --> 01:12:53,932
So, I mean, all those rule followers have been parking in the direction of travel.

860
01:12:54,412 --> 01:13:01,275
I understand it hasn't been enforced, but... I wasn't aware that it was a law until it came up this year.

861
01:13:01,935 --> 01:13:03,376
Yeah, definitely is.

862
01:13:04,656 --> 01:13:06,817
So... I have a quick question.

863
01:13:07,778 --> 01:13:15,681
If you have an issue where your group is the better group to evaluate a situation for safety or ease,

864
01:13:18,023 --> 01:13:21,105
Can the community make petitions to your group to evaluate?

865
01:13:21,725 --> 01:13:24,868
Because what I'm getting to is I really don't want to table this.

866
01:13:26,169 --> 01:13:35,116
But I love the idea of your group looking at this and deciding, look, for safety factors or ease of pushing snow, it's better for us to look at this.

